About this job:<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />
LocalResponse is seeking an intelligent, articulate, and energetic Sales Planner to join our New York team. The Sales Planner will play a critical role in the selling process by working closely with the Sales and Account Management teams in delivering world-class client proposals. This is an excellent opportunity to be part of an online advertising industry leader and contribute to our tremendous growth. This position offers an excellent opportunity for career advancement into sales or client services.</p>
<p>
Responsibilities:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Manage, process, and coordinate the on-time delivery of client proposals</li>
<li>
Schedule and conduct proposal strategy sessions with objective of producing campaign plans aligned closely with the advertiser&#39;s campaign goals</li>
<li>
Utilize research and inventory reporting tools, including Google&#39;s Invite Media, TubeMogul, etc.</li>
<li>
Offer solutions to RFP objectives utilizing past data on previous campaigns while offering new LocalResponse products</li>
<li>
Manage proposal database and generate weekly proposal reporting</li>
<li>
Review marketing materials and assemble information</li>
<li>
Work relentlessly to meet the team&#39;s objectives</li>
<li>
Communicate effectively between multiple departments (account management, sales, planning, etc.)</li>
</ul>
<p>
Qualifications:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Knowledge of the online advertising industry, trends, technologies, and pricing models (CPM, CPC, CPA)</li>
<li>
Understanding of online ad campaign metrics and analysis</li>
<li>
College Degree and/or a minimum 1-2 year experience preferably working in the Internet advertising industry (Media Planning experience a plus)</li>
<li>
Strong skills working with Excel and PowerPoint (SalesForce, MediaVisor)</li>
<li>
Professional maturity, integrity, discipline and a positive attitude</li>
<li>
Excellent written communication skills and multitasking abilities</li>
<li>
Highly energized and motivated by achievement and success</li>
</ul>
<p>
About LocalResponse:</p>
<p>
LocalResponse helps marketers respond to social intent. Based in Chelsea NYC, LocalResponse is co-founded by digital advertising pioneers Nihal Mehta (founder ipsh!, sold to Omnicom in 2005 &amp; early investor in Admob), Kathy Leake (co-founder Media6Degrees), and Michael Muse. LocalResponse works with Fortune 500 advertisers such as Audi, Coca-Cola, Dell, FedEx, General Electric, General Mills, General Motors, Hershey&rsquo;s, Kmart, Loews, McDonald&#39;s, Microsoft, NBC-Universal, etc, We make sure we maintain a &ldquo;work hard, play hard&rdquo; mentality at LocalResponse though weekly happy hours, ping-pong tournaments, company outings, etc.</p>
