			<description><![CDATA[<p>
About Us:</p>
<p>
LocalResponse aggregates intent data through multiple social networks and location based services. We believe social signals are the most declarative form of intent for a marketer. We define intent as someone publicly posting what they are doing on Twitter, checking into a location using a location based service like Foursquare, or publicly expressing relevant sentiment.</p>
<p>
LocalResponse turns all of this social intent into targetable impressions and call this&hellip;. Intent Targeting.</p>
<p>
About the Account Executive:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Responsible for identifying, qualifying and closing new business opportunities from top tier consumer marketers and their advertising agencies as well as from a variety of online direct response advertisers.</li>
<li>
This position is accountable for generating revenue from major accounts and for developing and managing long term relationships with senior marketing, advertising and executive level contacts within client and agency organizations across industry verticals.</li>
<li>
Top candidates for this position will be confident, organized, and love the thrill of closing new business.</li>
<li>
Working in a fast-paced, results-oriented environment, the AE will be comfortable in new sales situations and will enjoy face-to-face sales.</li>
<li>
We are seeking goal-oriented, motivated salespeople to join our Sales Team.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Qualifications:</p>
<ul>
<li>
3-5 years of digital media sales experience, network and mobile experience are a plus!</li>
<li>
Demonstrated history of quota attainment; ability to evaluate sound business opportunities AND close deals.</li>
<li>
Seasoned prospecting skills (relating to internet/online advertising)</li>
<li>
Excellent communication and presentation skills.</li>
<li>
Strong relationships with marketers and agencies in their region.</li>
<li>
Propensity to adapt to changing environments.</li>
<li>
Ability to work in local or remote office; travel as needed to accomplish business goals.</li>
</ul>
<p>
LocalResponse:</p>
<p>
LocalResponse makes mobile, tablet and desktop ads more contextual by using social conversations to target the right audience. Based in Chelsea NYC, LocalResponse is co-founded by digital advertising pioneers Nihal Mehta (founder ipsh!, sold to Omnicom in 2005 and early investor in Admob), Kathy Leake (co-founder Media6Degrees), and Michael Muse; and works with over 250 advertisers including Audi, Cadbury-Adams, Coca-Cola, Dell, Estee Lauder, FedEx, General Electric, General Mills, General Motors, Hershey&rsquo;s, Kmart, Loews, McDonald&rsquo;s, Microsoft, NBC-Universal, Pepsi, Verizon and Walgreens.</p>
]]></description>
